name: Fernando Valenzuela death
summary: The news headlines collectively report the passing of renowned former Major League Baseball pitcher, Fernando Valenzuela, at the age of 63. Valenzuela, who played for the Los Angeles Dodgers, was celebrated for his distinctive screwball pitch that puzzled batters throughout his career. His legacy extends beyond his athletic achievements, as he became a symbol of immigration and inspired countless Mexican-American fans, igniting the phenomenon known as "Fernandomania." Valenzuela's remarkable life and tragic death serve as a reminder of the transformative power of immigration and the profound impact individuals can have, both on the baseball diamond and beyond.
